      "text": "The power of storytelling is understood in many cultures. For us at [[Griffin]], we too value it's power. We repeatedly tell our stories in an effort to keep our culture thriving, speaking of the seeds that sprouted the trees we dwell under. If you have a willing ear, we'll tell you the stories of our manifestation, there are many. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "7c925ff861f9e178",
      "text": "Storytelling allows us to share our why and connects people to our purpose. In the words of Simon Sinek, \"People don't buy what you do, they buy why you do it.\" In sharing our stories regularly, we keep our shared vision alive and frequently reinvigorate our momentum."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d1d2e7d932ee736f",
      "text": "At Griffin, we often tell the stories of our evolution through tales of our mantras, artefacts, rituals and traditions. We narrate how our practices, values and beliefs came to be and marvel at how they've morphed and shifted. Storytelling allows us to feel deeply connected to our work. Storytelling connects us to our deep truth, our why. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "aa24d3f4ad128967",
      "text": "Storytelling isn’t just reserved for the Griffin story. We also seek to hear the individual stories within our community. Our classroom walls tell stories of unfolding class learning, capturing thinking and how it changes over time. Our learners share stories about their individual learning journeys at our quarterly Celebration of Learning. Sharing and deeply listening to stories is part of our cultural identity. Rather than a simple sharing products of learning, the story of the process is seen and heard, too. "
    },
